{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35f44f6e-7813-4212-9bf8-382d72b76d26","content":"Here's the plan and architecture for your RAG-based Q&A feature:\n\n---\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌────────────────┐\n│  Markdown   │──────▶│  Ingestion       │──────▶│  Vector Store  │\n│  Docs/      │       │  (chunk + embed) │       │  (in-memory or │\n└─────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       │   persistent)  │\n                                                  └───────┬────────┘\n                                                          │\n┌─────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐               │\n│  User Query │──────▶│  Query Endpoint  │◀──────────────┘\n│  POST /ask  │       │  (embed → search │\n└─────────────┘       │   → LLM answer)  │\n                      └──────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Key Components\n\n| Layer | Responsibility | Suggested Approach |\n|-------|---------------|--------------------|\n| **Chunking** | Split markdown into overlapping passages (~500 tokens, ~100 overlap) | Recursive text splitter respecting heading boundaries |\n| **Embedding** | Convert chunks to vectors | `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` + OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` |\n| **Vector Store** | Store & retrieve by similarity | `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData` with in-memory provider (swap to Qdrant/Azure AI Search later) |\n| **Query Pipeline** | Embed question → top-K retrieval → prompt LLM with context | Semantic Kernel or raw `IChatClient` |\n| **LLM Answer** | Generate grounded response citing sources | GPT-4o via `Microsoft.Extensions.AI` |\n\n## Endpoints\n\n- **`POST /ingest`** — Reads all `Docs/*.md`, chunks, embeds, and upserts into the vector store. Returns chunk count.\n- **`POST /ask`** — Accepts `{ \"question\": \"...\" }`, retrieves top-5 chunks, sends them + question to the LLM, returns `{ \"answer\": \"...\", \"sources\": [...] }`.\n\n## NuGet Packages Needed\n\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.OpenAI` — chat + embedding abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.Abstractions` — vector store abstraction\n- `Microsoft.Extensions.VectorData.InMemory` — dev-time store\n- `Markdig` — parse markdown structure for heading-aware chunking\n\n## Design Decisions\n\n1. **Chunking strategy**: Split on `##` headings first, then recursively split oversized sections. Preserves semantic coherence.\n2. **Overlap**: 100-token overlap between chunks prevents losing context at boundaries.\n3. **Metadata**: Each chunk stores `{ fileName, heading, chunkIndex }` for source attribution.\n4. **Grounding prompt**: System prompt instructs the LLM to answer *only* from provided context and cite the source file/heading.\n5. **No external infra for MVP**: In-memory vector store keeps the first iteration dependency-free.\n\n## File Structure (proposed)\n\n```\nProductQA/\n├── Controllers/\n│   └── QAController.cs          # /ingest and /ask endpoints\n├── Services/\n│   ├── DocumentChunker.cs       # Markdown-aware chunking logic\n│   ├── IngestionService.cs      # Orchestrates chunk → embed → store\n│   └── QueryService.cs          # Orchestrates embed → search → LLM\n├── Models/\n│   ├── DocumentChunk.cs         # Chunk record with vector + metadata\n│   └── AskRequest/Response.cs   # DTOs\n├── Docs/\n│   ├── configuration.md\n│   └── getting-started.md\n├── Program.cs                   # DI registration\n└── ProductQA.csproj\n```\n\n---\n\nWant me to implement this?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b5bf5ae-cf36-4d15-8c00-017e0176f6bb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a good picture. This is a minimal .NET 10 Web API with two markdown docs. Let me create a comprehensive architecture plan.","outputTokens":1021,"requestId":"A402:BF033:288B6B6:2CD549B:69FD33D9"},"id":"67b056a9-d2fa-4e17-8c39-d456e5ec20d7","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:53:03.116Z","parentId":"477badc2-12a3-46c5-b959-df91c97bf5c5"}
